    "overview": "Meghalaya, the Abode of Clouds, is India's best-kept secret — a northeastern paradise of living root bridges, crystal-clear rivers, dramatic waterfalls, limestone caves, and the wettest place on earth. Shillong's colonial charm, Cherrapunji's rain-soaked wonders, and Dawki's transparent Umngot River offer experiences unlike anywhere else in India. This is raw, untouched India at its most spectacular.",
